- [Dependencies](#dependencies)
- [Bonus](#bonus)
- [Contributing](#contributing)

## Overview

In this project, we create a module `geometrical_shapes` where we define several geometrical shapes (Point, Line, Triangle, Rectangle, Circle) and traits (Drawable, Displayable). Using these shapes, we generate a 1000x1000 PNG image with a variety of shapes randomly placed within the image.

The primary objectives are:
- Implementing the `Drawable` and `Displayable` traits for the shapes.
- Defining structures for different shapes like Point, Line, Triangle, Rectangle, and Circle.
- Working with random generation of coordinates for shapes.
- Saving the generated shapes to a PNG image.

## Usage

To use this project, simply clone the repository and run it with `cargo run`:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/geometrical-shapes-rust.git
cd geometrical-shapes-rust
cargo run
